<h1 class="off">A Traditional Understanding</h1><br>

HEALTH - DISEASE – PREVENTION: Western allopathic medicine has focused
mainly on the diagnosis of diseases and the means to make symptoms
disappear with solutions external to the individual. Natural medicine
and alternative therapies, with their more holistic approach, understand
most diseases as a warning that the body gives us to indicate that
something is wrong and must be changed. Seen in this way, illness is an
opportunity that makes us tune into our interior, reflect on and review our
life. Pain can be a result of inadequate living and eating habits, overthinking,
and unresolved mental or emotional issues that can not be expressed in
any other way.  How much fear, anger, anger, loneliness, sadness,
frustration or any other repressed emotion do we express through pain and
illness? Silencing the symptoms with toxic pharmaceuticals, most of
which have side effects, works as a short-term treatment of symptoms but
does not address the underlying causes. Almost all health systems based on
passivity and dependence on the patient have failed since authentic healing
is an active process involving participation and awakening of the individual
to achieve transformation.
<br><br>
Considering health as the state of unity,
balance and harmony between the different levels of being Jing, Qi and
Shen: Physical, Energetic and Spiritual and between being and its
environment (nature), prevention will consist of knowing, understanding
and applying the principles or Universal Laws to one’s own life.  As we
become aware of ourselves (awakening) and harmonize with the being that
we are and what surrounds us (flow) we can transform our life. Change is
the only truth of the Universe; Whoever does not develop and grow
continuously stagnates; And therefore gets sick for going against a
natural law.
