Cosmetic acupuncture involves the stimulation and insertion through the skin of
small needles at specific points in areas of the face, neck, and other
parts of the body. The needles cause a contraction of the dermis (the inner
layer of the skin), the facial muscles are toned and the skin is
stretched. Stimulating the emission of endorphins, neurotransmitters, 
aminoacids and the activation of the nervous system.<br>

